  "prompt": "If you were born deaf, what language would you think in?",
  "response": "People who are born deaf often think in the language they are most familiar with, which is typically a sign language, such as American Sign Language (ASL) or British Sign Language (BSL), depending on their geographic location and the language they have been exposed to. For many deaf individuals, their thought processes may involve visual or spatial representations, rather than auditory or spoken language. Additionally, they can think in written forms of their native spoken language if they have learned to read and write it. The experience of thinking in a language is highly individualized and can vary widely among deaf people.",
